snippet.textDisplay:
April: People be wondering why the axe is upside down...

Me: Is it mmm ok here my logic... if you laid the axe on a table the blade edge be away from you and if you were to carry the axe the blade edge is away from you so blade up and away = upside down... Something I remember from being in boy scouts to be able to safely carrying an axe and safe positioning etc hehehe.

snippet.textDisplay:
You've come a long, long way in a few years and you deserve the success because of your hard work, mixed with a lot of skills. I wish you every success with this huge expansion - you've obviously thought long and hard about this venture and it certainly looks impressive. With your skill set and the equipment you have accumulated, I'm sure you will do a lot of the alterations yourself, which should keep the overall cost down too. This "lockdown" we're all going through should give you some extra time to get things ready, prior to letting the public loose in "The Wood Shop". Employing some help is a great move. I hope he doesn't change your video style too much but, not having to edit everything yourself, will save you so much time.
Cheers for now lass and good luck,
Dougie.
Oh, P.S. Who knew you owned a short skirt - suits you?👌
